HEADWORD: Elixate
<hw>E*lix"ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>elixatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>elixare</ets> to seethe, fr.
<ets>elixus</ets> thoroughly boiled; <ets>e</ets> + <ets>lixare</ets> to
boil, <ets>lix</ets> ashes.]</ety> <def>To boil; to seethe; hence, to
extract by boiling or seething.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cockeram.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elixation</ent>⟦br⟧
